ps%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a840828ed31300199e1b50%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElon%20Musk%20was%20always%20going%20to%20destroy%20Twitter.%20The%20real%20surprise%20is%20how%20fast%20he%20was%20able%20to%20wreck%20it.%3Cp%3EJenny%20Chang-Rodriguez%2FInsider%3B%20Chesnot%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EElon%20Musk%20has%20killed%20the%20one%20thing%20that%20made%20Twitter%20special%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20less%20than%20a%20year%20since%20he%20bought%20it%2C%20and%20Elon%20Musk's%20Twitter%20is%20already%20well%20on%20its%20way%20to%20suffering%20a%20fate%20worse%20than%20death%20%E2%80%94%20irrelevance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20platform%2C%20which%20Musk%20promised%20to%20turn%20into%20a%20free-speech%2C%20bot-free%20haven%2C%20is%20glitchier%2C%20bottier%2C%20and%20spammier%20than%20ever.%20In%20May%2C%20when%20Gov.%20Ron%20DeSantis%20of%20Florida%20announced%20his%20presidential%20candidacy%20on%20Twitter%2C%20a%20parade%20of%20malfunctions%20turned%20what%20should%20have%20been%20a%20historic%20moment%20for%20the%20company%20into%20a%20mess.%20Twitter%20hasn't%20even%20been%20able%20to%20hold%20it%20together%20during%20the%20news-making%20events%20it's%20known%20for%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-rihanna-super-bowl-outage-despite-elon-musks-best-efforts-2023-2%5C%22%3ERihanna%20was%20performing%20at%20the%20Super%20Bowl%20halftime%20show%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20pretty%20much%20every%20new%20%26quot%3Bfeature%26quot%3B%20that%20Musk%20rolls%20out%20%E2%80%94%20from%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20length%20of%20tweets%20to%20the%20now%20infamous%20%26quot%3Brate%20limit%26quot%3B%20that%20prevents%20users%20from%20seeing%20more%20than%20a%20set%20number%20of%20tweets%20a%20day%20%E2%80%94%20has%20made%20the%20product%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwitter%20is%20at%20its%20core%20an%20advertising%20business%20%E2%80%94%20the%20last%20public%20financials%20showed%20that%20over%2090%25%20of%20its%20revenue%20came%20from%20ads.%20To%20succeed%20in%20that%20business%2C%20it%20needs%20both%20the%20users%20who%20generate%20content%20and%20the%20clients%20who%20buy%20ads%20to%20believe%20it%20is%20a%20stable%2C%20reliable%20place.%20If%20an%20advertising%20platform%20can't%20be%20trusted%20during%20the%20Super%20Bowl%20of%20advertising%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Super%20Bowl%20%E2%80%94%20then%20what%20good%20is%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20now%20there%20is%20growing%20competition.%20On%20Thursday%20%E2%80%94%20a%20couple%20of%20weeks%20after%20Musk%20challenged%20him%20to%20a%20cage%20fight%20%E2%80%94%20Mark%20Zuckerberg's%20Meta%20launched%20Threads%2C%20a%20social-note%20site%20fused%20with%20Instagram.%20In%20less%20than%2024%20hours%2C%20Threads%20had%20over%2030%20million%20users%2C%20including%20Rep.%20Alexandria%20Ocasio-Cortez%2C%20Jennifer%20Lopez%2C%20and%20Steph%20Curry.%20For%20Musk%2C%20this%20should%20be%20more%20embarrassing%20than%20getting%20wrecked%20in%20the%20ring.%20Clearly%20in%20some%20kind%20of%20mood%20over%20Threads'%20overnight%20success%2C%20he%20wrote%20on%20Twitter%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20infinitely%20preferable%20to%20be%20attacked%20by%20strangers%20on%20Twitter%2C%20than%20indulge%20in%20the%20false%20happiness%20of%20hide-the-pain%20Instagram.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYeah%2C%20OK%2C%20chief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20relevant%20was%20Twitter's%20core%20strength%20as%20a%20platform.%20It%20never%20really%20made%20money%2C%20and%20it%20was%20never%20the%20biggest%20social%20network.%20But%20when%20something%20was%20happening%2C%20people%20immediately%20went%20to%20Twitter%20to%20know%20more.%20Its%20appeal%20was%20its%20ability%20to%20collect%20information%20about%20the%20present%20moment%2C%20whether%20it%20was%20the%20death%20of%20a%20notable%20member%20of%20society%2C%20a%20weather%20event%2C%20or%20traffic.%20Unfortunately%2C%20Musk's%20fumbling%20is%20rubbing%20all%20that%20relevance%20away%20and%20giving%20other%20platforms%20an%20opening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20has%20said%20he%20might%20turn%20Twitter%20into%20an%20%26quot%3Beverything%20app%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20one-stop%20shop%20for%20anything%20from%20ride-hailing%20to%20shopping.%20But%20what's%20more%20likely%20is%20that%20he%20will%20turn%20it%20into%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20Truth%20Social%20%E2%80%94%20a%20digital%20megaphone%20for%20a%20single%2C%20raging%20narcissist%20and%20all%20the%20people%20who%20fawn%20over%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20you%20do%20a%20turnaround%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%20days%20of%20Musk's%20Twitter%20takeover%2C%20I%20told%20you%20he%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-takeover-money-sucking-quagmire-tesla-spacex-debt-2022-4%5C%22%3Eoverpaying%20for%20the%20company%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Once%20the%20deal%20went%20through%2C%20I%20said%20he%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-business-playbook-boss-visionary-jerk-spacex-tesla-twitter-2022-12%5C%22%3Eno%20real%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20turn%20the%20business%20around.%20In%20those%20respects%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20fair%20to%20say%20I%20was%20right.%20That%20said%2C%20all%20this%20is%20unraveling%20much%20quicker%20than%20I%20thought%20it%20would.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwitter%20certainly%20needed%20a%20turnaround.%20Even%20before%20the%20takeover%2C%20it%20needed%20new%20management%2C%20a%20reevaluation%20of%20the%20business%2C%20and%20investment%20in%20product%20innovation%20to%20bring%20in%20new%20users.%20Unfortunately%20for%20Twitter%2C%20Musk%20is%20not%20a%20traditional%20turnaround%20guy.%20In%20fact%2C%20he's%20not%20a%20turnaround%20guy%20at%20all.%20All%20the%20businesses%20he%20has%20started%20were%20first%20movers%20in%20nascent%20industries.%20What%20made%20those%20businesses%20successful%20won't%20work%20at%20Twitter%2C%20but%20Musk%20tried%20it%20anyway.%20He%20fired%20over%2070%25%20of%20Twitter's%20staff%20with%20absolutely%20no%20respect%20for%20their%20institutional%20knowledge.%20He%20acted%20as%20if%20he%20alone%20could%20be%20the%20advertising%20business%20(like%20he%20was%20at%20Tesla).%20And%20he%20didn't%20bother%20to%20get%20to%20know%20what%20users%20wanted%20out%20of%20their%20Twitter%2C%20assuming%20instead%20that%20his%20hopeless%20addiction%20to%20tweeting%20had%20already%20given%20him%20all%20the%20answers.%20But%20unsurprisingly%2C%20being%20a%20billionaire%20%26quot%3Breply%20guy%26quot%3B%20does%20not%20give%20one%20a%20clear%20sense%20of%20why%20everyday%20people%20are%20using%20the%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20give%20you%20an%20example.%20For%20years%2C%20the%20Metropolitan%20Transportation%20Authority%2C%20the%20agency%20that%20controls%20New%20York%20City's%20subways%20and%20buses%2C%20used%20Twitter%20to%20send%20out%20automated%20alerts%20about%20emergencies%20and%20service%20changes.%20It%20was%20a%20symbiotic%20relationship%20for%20the%20site%20%E2%80%94%20users%20depended%20on%20the%20platform%20for%20timely%20updates%20about%20stalled%20trains%20and%20late%20buses%2C%20while%20the%20MTA%20had%20a%20quick%2C%20reliable%20way%20to%20reach%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20decided%20in%20April%20to%20abruptly%20cut%20off%20access%20to%20the%20Twitter%20program%20that%20allowed%20the%20MTA%20to%20send%20out%20automated%20alerts%20after%20it%20ran%20relatively%20smoothly%20for%20years.%20Musk%20%E2%80%94%20who%20is%20frantically%20looking%20for%20cash%20in%20Twitter's%20couch%20cushions%20%E2%80%94%20wanted%20to%20charge%20users%20for%20access%20to%20this%20feed%2C%20known%20as%20Twitter's%20application%20programming%20interface.%20He%20thought%20that%20national%20weather%20services%2C%20governments%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2023%2F4%2F21%2F23691784%2Felon-musk-twitter-disaster-alert-accounts-fire-storm-tsunami-earthquake%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemergency-response%20agencies%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20needed%20Twitter%20more%20than%20Twitter%20needed%20them.%20The%20MTA%20estimated%20it%20could%20cost%20it%20%2450%2C000%20a%20month%20to%20retain%20access%2C%20but%20instead%20of%20paying%20up%2C%20it%20called%20his%20bluff.%20The%20MTA%20returned%20only%20when%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farstechnica.com%2Ftech-policy%2F2023%2F05%2Ftwitter-just-realized-it-was-dumb-to-cut-off-automated-public-service-tweets%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMusk%20reversed%20his%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20allowed%20government%20agencies%20to%20come%20back%20at%20no%20charge.%20The%20situation%20forced%20Musk%20to%20show%20his%20hand%2C%20and%20it%20was%20a%20weak%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20only%20difference%20with%20Twitter%20and%20Musk's%20other%20companies%20is%20that%20he's%20treating%20Twitter%20users%20worse%20than%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-firing-workers-accident-hr-2022-11%3Fop%3D1%5C%22%3Etreats%20his%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Vicki%20Bryan%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20bond-research%20service%20Bond%20Angle%2C%20told%20me%20over%20the%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwitter's%20product%20is%20also%20suffering%20because%20Musk%20notoriously%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-rate-limits-cut-costs-former-employee-elon-musk-2023-7%5C%22%3Edoesn't%20pay%20his%20bills%20on%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20tendency%20that%20has%20frustrated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-sued-by-lebronze-alloys-supplier-for-17-million-2019-5%5C%22%3ETesla's%20suppliers%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20years.%20Now%20it's%20frustrating%20Twitter's%20landlords%20and%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20which%20is%20holding%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F6bf11c8e-c3f3-40cb-9489-157db427602a%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebad%20property%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20Musk%20refuses%20to%20pay%20the%20rent%20for%20a%20handful%20of%20the%20company's%20offices.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20you%20read%20between%20the%20headlines%2C%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-faces-700000-unpaid-bills-lawsuit-including-office-clear-out-2023-7%5C%22%3Ewhiffs%20of%20Musk's%20miserliness%20everywhere%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Just%20before%20the%20July%204%20holiday%2C%20he%20announced%20that%20the%20site%20would%20begin%20limiting%20the%20number%20of%20tweets%20users%20could%20see%20in%20a%20single%20day.%20He%20claimed%20it%20was%20to%20improve%20the%20experience%20and%20get%20at%20those%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortune.com%2F2023%2F07%2F05%2Flinda-yaccarino-elon-musk-twitter-limits-tweets-ceo-speaks-out%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epesky%20bots%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20that's%20true%2C%20Musk%20is%20sacrificing%20Twitter's%20reputation%20as%20a%20trusted%20destination%20for%20breaking%20news%20and%20free-flowing%20conversation%20to%20fight%20spam.%20That's%20like%20lighting%20a%20house%20on%20fire%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20termites.%20The%20strategy%20makes%20more%20sense%20if%20it's%20actually%20a%20misdirection%20from%20Musk's%20penurious%20mismanagement.%20As%20of%20late%20June%2C%20Twitter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-elon-musk-oracle-bills-larry-ellison-2023-6%5C%22%3Ehadn't%20paid%20its%20database%20provider%20Oracle%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20months.%20And%20last%20month%2C%20CEO%20Linda%20Yaccarino%20had%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-google-cloud-bills-invoices-linda-yaccarino-payments-2023-6%5C%22%3Esettle%20Twitter's%20outstanding%3C%2Fa%3E%20bill%20with%20Google%20Cloud%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-stopped-paying-google-cloud-bills-money-platformer-2023-6%5C%22%3Eprovides%20a%20home%20for%20Twitter's%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20well%20as%20other%20computing%20services.%20It's%20unclear%20how%20the%20company%20would%20survive%20without%20the%20infrastructure%20these%20companies%20provide%2C%20and%20it's%20almost%20certain%20that%20these%20are%20not%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-responded-to-unpaid-bill-emails-with-automated-bot-report-2023-5%5C%22%3Eonly%20critical%20business%20relationships%3C%2Fa%3E%20Musk%20has%20put%20at%20risk.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20sure%2C%20maybe%20limiting%20user%20access%20to%20the%20site%20is%20about%20the%20bots.%20Maybe%2C%20to%20Musk%2C%20that's%20a%20crusade%20worth%20sacrificing%20the%20very%20thing%20that%20makes%20Twitter%20special.%20Maybe%20he%20thinks%20fighting%20the%20bots%20is%20worth%20shrinking%20Twitter%20%E2%80%94%20a%20social-media%20site%20that%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20grow%20its%20user%20base%20for%20years.%20But%20it%20seems%20much%20more%20likely%20that%20the%20site%20is%20under%20pressure%20from%20understaffing%2C%20weak%20infrastructure%2C%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-let-them-sue-response-twitters-unpaid-pills-report-2023-3%5C%22%3EC-suite%20full%20of%20cheap%20dilettantes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20anyone%20has%20any%20bright%20ideas%20over%20at%20Twitter%20%E2%80%94%20aside%20from%20charging%20for%20a%20blue%20checkmark%20no%20one%20wants%20anymore%20%E2%80%94%20now%20is%20the%20time%20to%20share%20them.%20In%20May%2C%20Fidelity%2C%20the%20giant%20mutual%20fund%20that%20retained%20its%20stake%20in%20Twitter%20through%20Musk's%20purchase%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Ftwitter-fidelity-musk-value-08c64f3bda6c3070fef0d33f247501a3%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Fidelity%2520Blue%2520Chip%2520Growth%2Cits%2520stake%2520at%2520in%2520October.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emarked%20down%20its%20valuation%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20company%20in%20May%20to%20%246.5%20million%20from%20about%20%2420%20million%20in%20October.%20That's%20about%20one-third%20of%20what%20it%20once%20was.%20Bryan%20has%20been%20following%20the%20saga%20of%20the%20%2413%20billion%20worth%20of%20debt%20that%20Musk%20had%20to%20load%20onto%20Twitter%20to%20take%20it%20over.%20She%20told%20me%20that%20in%20her%20decades%20of%20experience%2C%20she%20had%20never%20seen%20a%20company%20deteriorate%20in%20value%20so%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwitter's%20true%20price%20isn't%20the%20%2444%20billion%20Musk%20paid%3B%20it's%20a%20falling%20knife%20%E2%80%94%20and%20everyone%20on%20Wall%20Street%20knows%20it.%20That's%20why%20banks%20such%20as%20Morgan%20Stanley%2C%20which%20signed%20on%20to%20sell%20Twitter's%20%2412.5%20million%20in%20debt%2C%20are%20simply%20sitting%20on%20piles%20of%20bonds%20and%20hoping%20for%20a%20miracle%2C%20rather%20than%20suffering%20the%20debasement%20of%20selling%20them%20for%20pennies%20on%20the%20dollar.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fleveraged-loan-logjam-eases-after-banks-unload-tens-of-billions-of-debt-122e652b%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Twitter's%20debt%20makes%20up%20the%20majority%20of%20what's%20left%20of%20the%20%2480%20billion%20pile%20of%20%26quot%3Bhung%20debt%26quot%3B%20sitting%20on%20banks'%20balance%20sheets%20%E2%80%94%20bonds%20from%20various%20acquisitions%20that%20no%20one%20wants%20to%20buy%20because%20now%20that%20interest%20rates%20are%20higher%2C%20the%20whole%20deal%20market%20has%20slowed%20down.%20Higher%20interest%20on%20debt%20also%20means%20Twitter's%20debt%20payments%20are%20more%20expensive.%20That%20leaves%20little%20room%20for%20error%20or%20experimentation%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20investing%20in%20Twitter%20as%20a%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Elon%20asks%20the%20banks%20for%20more%20money%2C%20they're%20going%20to%20say%2C%20'Sorry%2C%20driving%20through%20a%20tunnel%2C%20can't%20hear%20you%2C'%26quot%3B%20Bryan%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20people%20you%20sold%20your%20debt%20to%20can't%20sell%20it%2C%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20get%20more%20debt.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EElon's%20the%20product%20now%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20products%20suck%2C%20users%20leave%2C%20and%20that's%20what's%20happening%20at%20Twitter.%20A%20May%20survey%20by%20Pew%20Research%20found%20high-frequency%20users%20were%20still%20around%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F05%2F17%2Fhow-us-adults-on-twitter-use-the-site-in-the-elon-musk-era%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebut%20posting%3C%2Fa%3E%20less.%20Part%20of%20the%20problem%20is%20that%20%E2%80%94%20like%20Truth%20Social%20%E2%80%94%20Musk%20has%20become%20the%20centerpiece%20of%20the%20website.%20Part%20of%20that%20is%20intentional.%20When%20Musk%20found%20out%20that%20his%20popularity%20was%20declining%20among%20users%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffinance.yahoo.com%2Fnews%2Felon-musk-reportedly-ordered-twitter-053546868.html%3Fguccounter%3D1%26guce_referrer%3DaHR0cHM6Ly9kdWNrZHVja2dvLmNvbS8%26guce_referrer_sig%3DAQAAAEeO4xiEpxAbwICqwEz3BHeKzz6IpbIvnF6cKoN4Y3jRViUS0OJbmVXUJQjux8DCXFs6MkWxFLzcyOL53BnIH0U9CB90WBeNgylQVWy7H0A0VDpb_BEr88xKZZWnAGV42egbPmIP1HZPtpVEVjHvHVFGpmKqXFqi3JvCH1M6zbLD%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eordered%20his%20engineers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20make%20his%20tweets%20more%20prominent.%20Another%20problem%20is%20that%20Musk%20attracts%20the%20very%20bots%20he%20complained%20about%20ad%20nauseam.%20Another%20Pew%20survey%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F05%2F17%2Fmajority-of-us-twitter-users-say-theyve-taken-a-break-from-the-platform-in-the-past-year%2F%3Forg%3D982%26lvl%3D100%26ite%3D11811%26lea%3D2479545%26ctr%3D0%26par%3D1%26trk%3Da0D3j000013SygtEAC%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E60%25%20of%20users%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20taken%20a%20break%20from%20Twitter%20over%20the%20past%20year.%20Call%20it%20what%20you%20want%2C%20but%20I'm%20going%20to%20go%20ahead%20and%20say%20they%20were%20suffering%20from%20%26quot%3BElon%20exhaustion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20Twitter%20alternatives%20for%20months%2C%20Mastodon%2C%20Post%2C%20Bluesky%20(from%20the%20Twitter%20founder%20Jack%20Dorsey)%20%E2%80%94%20take%20your%20pick.%20Those%20sites%20have%20been%20picking%20off%20Twitter%20fanatics%20little%20by%20little%2C%20fragmenting%20users%20and%20denying%20any%20one%20site%20the%20critical%20mass%20to%20match%20Twitter's%20ceaseless%20chatter.%20They%20haven't%20attracted%20the%20celebrities%2C%20the%20brands%2C%20or%20all%20the%20other%20cultural%20kitsch%20that%20we%20love%20to%20hate.%20But%20the%20rocket%20launch%20of%20Meta's%20Threads%20appears%20to%20be%20the%20most%20serious%20threat%20to%20Musk's%20Twitter%20yet.%20The%20difference%20with%20Threads%20is%20that%20%E2%80%94%20because%20of%20its%20seamless%20connection%20to%20Instagram%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20not%20picking%20off%20Twitter%20users%3B%20it's%20scooping%20them%20away%20with%20a%20dump%20truck%20and%20hauling%20them%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20may%20have%20something%20to%20say%20about%20this.%20FTC%20Chair%20Lina%20Khan%20has%20tried%20to%20sue%20Meta%20for%20copying%20products%20from%20smaller%20companies%20to%20maintain%20market%20dominance%20in%20social%20media.%20But%20so%20far%2C%20her%20argument%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fftc-loses-antitrust-challenge-to-facebook-parent-meta-11675272525%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehasn't%20worked%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20somehow%20I%20doubt%20helping%20Musk%20will%20give%20her%20heightened%20impetus%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20drawing%20board.%20For%20Musk's%20part%2C%20his%20lawyers%20have%20already%20written%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-threatens-sue-meta-mark-zuckerberg-threads-lawsuit-2023-7%5C%22%3Ecease-and-desist%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20telling%20Meta%20that%20Twitter%20will%20sue%20if%20Threads%20is%20not%20taken%20down%20%E2%80%94%20thus%20offering%20Zuckerberg%20the%20opportunity%20to%20beat%20Musk%20in%20a%20courtroom%20as%20well%20as%20in%20a%20cage.%20Congratulations%20to%20all%20the%20lawyers%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20her%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20Yaccarino%20seems%20a%20competent%20professional%20who%20probably%20doesn't%20need%20my%20advice%2C%20but%20I'm%20going%20to%20give%20it%20to%20her%20anyway%3A%20Run!%20Musk%20is%20known%20for%20micromanaging%20and%20penny%20pinching%2C%20which%20means%20your%20expertise%20will%20be%20subverted%20to%20his%20ego%20in%20all%20decision-making.%20And%20when%20you%20finally%20want%20to%20leave%2C%20he'll%20fight%20you%20for%20every%20penny%20you%20deserve%20all%20the%20way%20out%20the%20door.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteslas-general-counsel-dane-butswinkas-leaves-after-2019-2%5C%22%3EI've%20seen%20this%20happen%20at%20Tesla%3C%2Fa%3E%20many%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20Musk%20has%20been%20able%20to%20fuse%20his%20brand%20with%20his%20products%20and%20turn%20them%20into%20a%20success.%20At%20Twitter%2C%20that%20fusion%20has%20turned%20the%20brand%20and%20the%20product%20into%20a%20toxic%20mess.%20And%20if%20Twitter%20is%20too%20toxic%20to%20be%20the%20global%20watercooler%2C%20it's%20diminished.%20The%20lights%20may%20be%20on%20%E2%80%94%20thanks%20to%20Musk's%20billions%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20only%20people%20home%20will%20be%20him%2C%20some%20misguided%20men%20who%20wish%20he%20were%20their%20dad%2C%20and%20porn%20bots.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20whether%20any%20app%20will%20be%20the%20%26quot%3BTwitter%20kil