n%20the%20well%20of%20the%20House.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22MADAN%20KUMAR%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fpatna%2Frow-over-tejashwi-yadav-bjp-members-create-ruckus-in-bihar-assembly-speaker-compelled-to-adjourned-proceedings-till-thursday%2Farticleshow%2F101694182.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Study%20Says%20%5C%22Underground%20Climate%20Change%5C%22%20Threatening%20Highrise%20Buildings%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20ground%20beneath%20us%20is%20heating%20up%2C%20giving%20rise%20to%20the%20phenomenon%20of%20%26quot%3Bunderground%20climate%20change%26quot%3B%20and%20our%20civil%20infrastructure%20was%20not%20designed%20for%20it%2C%20scientists%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20continuous%20heat%20diffusion%20from%20buildings%20and%20underground%20transportation%2C%20seen%20in%20many%20urban%20areas%20around%20the%20world%2C%20causes%20the%20ground%20to%20warm%20at%20an%20alarming%20rate%2C%20found%20to%20be%200.1%20to%202.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20per%20decade%20by%20researchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20heating%20up%20of%20ground%20leads%20to%20its%20deformation%20that%20includes%20both%20expansion%20and%20contraction%2C%20causing%20building%20foundations%20and%20the%20surrounding%20ground%20to%20move%20excessively%20and%20sometimes%20develop%20cracks%2C%20thereby%20impacting%20structures'%20long-term%20performance%20and%20durability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ground%20is%20deforming%20as%20a%20result%20of%20temperature%20variations%2C%20and%20no%20existing%20civil%20structure%20or%20infrastructure%20is%20designed%20to%20withstand%20these%20variations%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Northwestern%20University's%20Alessandro%20Rotta%20Loria%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20civil%20and%20environmental%20engineering%2C%20and%20who%20led%20the%20US-based%20study%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Communications%20Engineering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWarmer%20temperatures%20caused%20swelling%20and%20expansion%20of%20the%20ground%20by%20as%20much%20as%2012%20millimetres%20and%20contraction%20and%20sinking%20(beneath%20the%20building's%20weight)%20by%20as%20much%20as%208%20mm%2C%20the%20researchers%20found%20using%20simulations%20on%20sensor-obtained%20temperature%20data%20of%20Chicago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20said%20that%20while%20imperceptible%20to%20humans%2C%20the%20variation%20was%20more%20than%20what%20many%20building%20components%20and%20foundation%20systems%20can%20handle%20without%20compromising%20their%20operational%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20think%20about%20basements%2C%20parking%20garages%2C%20tunnels%20and%20trains%2C%20all%20of%20these%20facilities%20continuously%20emit%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20general%2C%20cities%20are%20warmer%20than%20rural%20areas%20because%20construction%20materials%20periodically%20trap%20heat%20derived%20from%20human%20activity%20and%20solar%20radiation%20and%20then%20release%20it%20into%20the%20atmosphere.%20That%20process%20has%20been%20studied%20for%20decades.%20Now%2C%20we%20are%20looking%20at%20its%20subsurface%20counterpart%2C%20which%20is%20mostly%20driven%20by%20anthropogenic%20activity%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rotta%20Loria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20team%20measured%20temperatures%2C%20above%20and%20below%20ground%2C%20by%20installing%20sensors%20across%20the%20Chicago%20Loop%2C%20the%20central%20business%20district%20of%20the%20city%20and%20the%20main%20section%20of%20Downtown%20Chicago%2C%20and%20beneath%20Grant%20Park%20along%20Lake%20Michigan%2C%20away%20from%20buildings%20and%20underground%20transportation%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubsurface%20temperatures%20beneath%20the%20Loop%20were%20often%20found%20to%20be%2010%20degrees%20warmer%20than%20those%20beneath%20Grant%20Park.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAir%20temperatures%20in%20underground%20structures%20can%20be%20up%20to%2025%20degrees%20higher%20compared%20to%20the%20undisturbed%20ground%20temperature%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20used%20Chicago%20as%20a%20living%20laboratory%2C%20but%20underground%20climate%20change%20is%20common%20to%20nearly%20all%20dense%20urban%20areas%20worldwide%2C%26quot%3B%20Rotta%20Loria%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20all%20urban%20areas%20suffering%20from%20underground%20climate%20change%20are%20prone%20to%20have%20problems%20with%20infrastructure.%20Future%20planning%20strategies%20should%20integrate%20geothermal%20technologies%20to%20harvest%20waste%20heat.%20Installing%20thermal%20insulation%20on%20buildings%20to%20minimise%20the%20heat%20entering%20the%20ground%20could%20also%20be%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20Rotta%20Loria%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689152460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2016-04%2Fgurgaon-indian-highrise-generic_650x400_81460469670.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fstudy-says-underground-climate-change-threatening-highrise-buildings-4200036%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20continuous%20heat%20diffusion%20from%20buildings%20and%20underground%20transportation%20causes%20the%20ground%20to%20warm%20at%20an%20alarming%20rate%2C%20the%20study%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fstudy-says-underground-climate-change-threatening-highrise-buildings-4200036%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fstudy-says-underground-climate-change-threatening-highrise-buildings-4200036%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fstudy-says-underground-climate-change-threatening-highrise-buildings-4200036%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20make%2