nsultation%2Fdiscussion%2Fworking%20papers%20on%20any%20of%20the%20issues%20pertaining%20to%20UCC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20the%2021st%20Law%20Commission%20of%20India%20in%20August%202018%20had%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20a%20UCC%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Flaw-commission-uniform-civil-code-notice%5C%22%3Eis%20neither%20necessary%20nor%20desirable%20at%20this%20stage%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9C%2C%20the%2022nd%20Law%20Commission%20issued%20a%20fresh%20notification.%20The%20latest%20panel%20does%20refer%20to%20the%20consultation%20paper%20published%20by%20the%20previous%20commission%20in%20August%202018%20but%20does%20not%20explain%20the%20reason%20for%20carrying%20out%20another%20round%20of%20consultations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20more%20than%20three%20years%20have%20lapsed%20from%20the%20date%20of%20issuance%20of%20the%20said%20consultation%20paper%2C%20bearing%20in%20mind%20the%20relevance%20and%20importance%20of%20the%20subject%20and%20also%20the%20various%20court%20orders%20on%20the%20subject%2C%20the%2022nd%20Law%20Commission%20considered%20it%20expedient%20to%20deliberate%20afresh%20over%20the%20subject%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20latest%20notification%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20members%20of%20the%2022nd%20Law%20Commission%20defended%20the%20latest%20notification%20while%20appearing%20before%20a%20parliamentary%20committee%20earlier%20this%20month.%20They%20said%20the%20last%20commission%20had%20brought%20out%20its%20suggestions%20in%202018%20and%20its%20term%20had%20also%20come%20to%20an%20end%2C%20and%20that%20is%20why%2C%20they%20have%20begun%20a%20fresh%20initiative%20which%20is%20essentially%20%E2%80%9Cinformational%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202018%2C%20a%20185-page%20consultation%20paper%20on%20%E2%80%9CReforms%20of%20Family%20Law%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%2021st%20Law%20Commission%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Flaw-commission-uniform-civil-code-notice%5C%22%3Ehad%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CCultural%20diversity%20cannot%20be%20compromised%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20our%20urge%20for%20uniformity%20itself%20becomes%20a%20reason%20for%20threat%20to%20the%20territorial%20integrity%20of%20the%20nation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20categorically%20stated%20that%20a%20unified%20nation%20does%20not%20necessarily%20need%20to%20have%20%E2%80%9Cuniformity%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9Cefforts%20have%20to%20be%20made%20to%20reconcile%20our%20diversity%20with%20universal%20and%20indisputable%20arguments%20on%20human%20rights%E2%80%9D.%20Differences%20do%20not%20always%20imply%20discrimination%20in%20a%20robust%20democracy%2C%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20top%20law%20advisory%20body%20had%20asserted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UCC%20is%20one%20of%20the%20ideological%20standpoints%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%2C%20which%20says%20that%20different%20property%20and%20matrimonial%20laws%20for%20people%20of%20different%20religions%20and%20denominations%20are%20an%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Flaw-commission-seeks-public-religious-bodies-views-uniform-civil-code-8663230%2F%5C%22%3Eaffront%20to%20national%20unity%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9C.%20It%20has%20relied%20on%20Article%2044%20of%20the%20constitution%20to%20push%20its%20view.%20The%20particular%20constitutional%20provision%20mandates%20the%20state%20to%20%E2%80%9Csecure%20for%20the%20citizens%20a%20uniform%20civil%20code%20throughout%20the%20territory%20of%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20made%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fin-poll-bound-madhya-pradesh-pm-modi-rakes-up-triple-talaq-ucc-and-appeasement%5C%22%3Estrong%20push%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20its%20favour%20at%20a%20recent%20political%20rally%20in%20Bhopal%2C%20which%20has%20once%20again%20spawned%20a%20debate%20on%20the%20contentious%20issue.%20Modi%20had%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CToday%20people%20are%20being%20instigated%20in%20the%20name%20of%20UCC.%20How%20can%20the%20country%20be%20run%20on%20two%20(laws)%3F%20The%20Constitution%20also%20talks%20of%20equal%20rights%E2%80%A6Supreme%20Court%20has%20also%20asked%20to%20implement%20UCC.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20further%20accused%20the%20Opposition%20of%20opposing%20the%20UCC%20for%20%E2%80%9Cvote%20bank%20politics%E2%80%9D.%20However%2C%20those%20opposed%20to%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20position%20view%20the%20UCC%20as%20a%20way%20for%20it%20to%20target%20minorities%2C%20particularly%20the%20Muslim%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689151518000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2F04101723%2FScreenshot-2022-05-04-at-10.17.19-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fas-deadline-nears-law-commission-receives-46-lakh-responses-on-uniform-civil-code%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20deadline%20for%20sending%20views%20on%20the%20contentious%20issue%20to%20the%20government's%20top%20law%20advisory%20body%20ends%20on%20July%2014.%20The%20Commission%20is%20likely%20to%20call%20certain%20organisations%20and%20people%20for%20a%20personal%20hearing%20in%20the%20coming%20days.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fas-deadline-nears-law-commission-receives-46-lakh-responses-on-uniform-civil-code%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Reliance%20Retail%20among%20three%20prospective%20buyers%20for%20Future%20Enterprises%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689151206000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2021-07%2F19%2Ffull%2F1626636528-6071.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Freliance-retail-among-three-prospective-buyers-for-future-enterprises-123071200398_1.html%2