0a%2022%20percent%20flat%20rate.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22AMBER%20BANERJEE%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22At%20SC%2C%20Modi%20Govt%20Justified%20S.K.%20Mishra's%20Extension%20Citing%20FATF%20Review.%20How%20Key%20Is%20His%20Role%20in%20it%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F11%2F15174623%2FSKMishra_EDdirector_141120_1200.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Union%20government%20had%20long%20since%20been%20buying%20time%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20the%20past%20two%20years%20to%20keep%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20head%20S.K.%20Mishra%20in%20office.%20The%20latest%20reason%20it%20has%20cited%20to%20argue%20for%20his%20extension%20is%20that%20there%20will%20be%20a%20Financial%20Action%20Task%20Force%20review%2C%20for%20which%20the%20director%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Ckey%20figure%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20FATF%20is%20an%20international%20terror-financing%20watchdog.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20now%20turns%20out%20the%20country%20review%20of%20the%20FATF%2C%20which%20began%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20will%20continue%20up%20to%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20well%20past%20the%20November%202023%20retirement%20date%20that%20the%20government%20had%20it%20mind%20for%20Mishra.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20the%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20refrained%20from%20telling%20the%20court%20is%20that%20a%20country%20is%20judged%20on%20at%20least%2040%20parameters%20and%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%E2%80%99s%20remit%20of%20money%20laundering%20and%20terror%20financing%20is%20just%20one%20of%20those%2040.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20fact%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fatf-gafi.org%2Fen%2Fcountries%2Fdetail%2FIndia.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20FATF%20website%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20says%20the%20lead%20ministry%20or%20authority%20for%20FATF%20is%20the%20Department%20of%20Economic%20Affairs.%20The%20other%20key%20authorities%20are%20Central%20Board%20of%20Excise%20and%20Customs%2C%20Financial%20Intelligence%20Unit%20(FIU)%20and%20the%20Union%20law%20ministry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ED%20reports%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Revenue.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20make%20a%20comparison%2C%20the%20FIU%20chief%2C%20Pankaj%20Mishra%2C%20in%20place%20since%202016%2C%20moved%20out%20of%20the%20department%20after%20having%20been%20prematurely%20repatriated%20in%202022.%20FIU%20is%20a%20key%20department%20dealing%20with%2C%20amongst%20other%20laws%2C%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%202002%2C%20just%20like%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMishra%20reports%20to%20the%20Revenue%20Secretary%20and%20since%202019%20the%20department%20has%20had%20three%20secretaries.%20The%20Department%20of%20Economic%20Affairs%20has%20followed%20a%20similar%20trajectory.%20%E2%80%9CSecretaries%20to%20the%20department%20play%20a%20key%20role%20and%20not%20a%20director%20of%20an%20investigative%20agency%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20an%20official%20privy%20to%20the%20FATF%20review.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-enforcement-directorate-sk-mishra-extensions-illegal%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Invalid%E2%80%99%3A%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Govt%E2%80%99s%20Extensions%20to%20ED%20Chief%20S.K.%20Mishra%20After%20Its%202021%20Order%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20FATF%20review%20is%20done%20every%2010%20years%20by%20a%20mutual%20assessment%20team%20drawn%20from%20the%2040%20member%20countries.%20The%20review%20is%20within%20an%2018-month%20time%20frame%20and%20began%20early%20this%20year.%20The%20final%20report%20will%20not%20be%20submitted%20before%20the%20end%20of%202024.%20India%20is%20a%20rare%20country%20whose%20FATF%20review%20has%20been%20postponed%20at%20least%20once%20on%20account%20of%20COVID-19.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20petitioner%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20cited%20FATF%20as%20the%20very%20basis%20for%20not%20giving%20an%20extension%20to%20the%20director.%20%E2%80%9CTo%20avoid%20the%20sudden%20break%20in%20continuity%20that%20would%20arise%20in%20November%202023%2C%20it%20would%20be%20more%20prudent%20to%20recruit%20a%20new%20Director%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%20so%20as%20to%20afford%20him%2Fher%20the%20maximum%20possible%20time%20before%20the%20mutual%20evaluations%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20petitioner%20had%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20mutual%20evaluation%20team%E2%80%99s%20key%20meeting%20in%20India%20is%20in%20November%20when%20the%20assessors%20will%20be%20doing%20an%20on-site%20visit%20to%20%E2%80%9Cverify%20and%20assess%20whether%20the%20systems%20in%20place%20are%20effective%20or%20not%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20per%20the%20FATF%20website.%20It%20is%20during%20this%20visit%20that%20assessors%20talk%20to%20government%20and%20private%20entities%20in%20order%20to%20evaluate%20a%20country%E2%80%99s%20performance.%20Or%20as%20SG%20Mehta%20told%20the%20court%20on%20a%20previous%20hearing%2C%20%E2%80%9CExperience%20has%20shown%20that%20having%20the%20laws%20in%20the%20books%20is%20not%20enough%2C%20the%20main%20focus%20is%20now%20on%20effectiveness.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fenforcement-directorate-sanjay-mishra-supreme-court-fatf%5C%22%3EUnion%20Govt%20Justifies%20ED%20Chief%E2%80%99s%20Extension%20Citing%20FATF%20Review%3B%20%E2%80%98Is%20There%20No%20Other%3F%E2%80%99%20Asks%20SC%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20this%20effectiveness%20that%20has%20the%20government%20worried%2C%20going%20by%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20performance%20statistics.%20Of%20the%20nearly%206%2C000%20cases%20filed%20since%20inception%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20conviction%20in%2024%20out%20of%2025%20cases%20in%20which%20a%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20trial%20was%20completed.%20Or%20as%20the%20ED%20would%20like%20to%20see%20the%20glass%20full%2C%20it%20has%20a%20conviction%20rate%20of%2094%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-the-enforcement-directorate-has-become-an-excessive-directorate%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20says%2C%20between%202018-19%20and%202021-22%2C%20cases%20registered%20by%20ED%20rose%20by%20505%25%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fnational%2F505-rise-in-cases-registered-by-ed-since-2018-1205886.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efrom%20195%20cases%20in%202018-19%2C%20to%201%2C180%20in%202021-22%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20number%20of%20searches%20the%20ED%20conducted%20rose%20by%20a%20huge%202%2C555%25%20between%202004-14%20and%202014-22.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20the%20Union%20finance%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20own%20data%2C%20112%20searches%20were%20carried%20out%20by%20the%20ED%20between%202004%20and%202014%20resulting%20in%20attachment%20of%20proceeds%20of%20crime%20worth%20Rs%205%2C346%20crore.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20sent%20a%20questionnaire%20to%20the%20ED.%20There%20are%20several%20questions%20that%20it%20did%20not%20respond%20to.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20how%20many%20cases%20has%20investigation%20been%20completed%20so%20that%20trial%20can%20commence%3F%20How%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Emany%20cases%20have%20been%20registered%20and%20closed%20by%20way%20of%20discharging%20or%20quashing%20or%20acquittal%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHow%20many%20accused%20have%20been%20discharged%20after%20a%20complaint%20was%20filed%20in%20court%3F%20Of%20the%20properties%20attached%2C%20how%20many%20have%20been%20confiscated%20so%20far%20by%20the%20ED%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20a%20June%202013%20plenary%20meeting%2C%20the%20FATF%20had%20%E2%80%9Cdecided%20that%20India%20had%20reached%20a%20satisfactory%20level%20of%20compliance%20with%20all%20of%20the%20core%20and%20key%20Recommendations%20and%20could%20be%20removed%20from%20the%20regular%20follow-up%20process%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20according%20to%20the%208%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20follow-up%20report%20on%20the%20mutual%20evaluation%20of%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689144114000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F11%2F15174623%2FSKMishra_EDdirector_141120_1200.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsk-mishra-enforcement-directorate-fatf-evaluation%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20country%20is%20judged%20on%20at%20least%2040%20parameters%20and%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate's%20remit%20of%20money%20laundering%20and%20terror%20financing%20is%20just%20one%20of%20those%2040.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsk-mishra-enforcement-directorate-fatf-evaluation%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22B'luru%3A%20Woman%20objects%20to%20bus%20conductor%20wearing%20skull%20cap%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689144003000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-101691478%2Cimgsize-40572.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbengaluru%2Fbengaluru-woman-objects-to-bmtc-bus-conductor-wearing-skull-cap-video-goes-viral%2Farticleshow%2F101689891.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20video%20of%20a%20woman%20passenger%20taking%20objection%20to%20a%20Bangalore%20Metropolitan%20Transport%20Corporation%20(BMTC)%20bus%20conductor%20wearing%20a%20skull%20cap%20while%20on%20duty%20has%20gone%20viral%20on%20social%20media.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22SUCHITH%20KIDIYOOR%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbengaluru%2Fbengaluru-woman-objects-to-bmtc-bus-conductor-wearing-skull-cap-video-goes-viral%2Farticleshow%2F101689891.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sun%20To%20Reach%20Solar%20Maximum%20In%202%20Years%2C%20May%20Lead%20To%20%5C%22Internet%20Apocalypse%5C%22%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20a%20renewed%20interest%20in%20the%20solar%20cycles%20of%20the%20Sun%20as%20it%20sends%20out%20solar%20storms%2C%20sometimes%20so%20devastating%20that%20they%20could%20snap%20all%20communication%20on%20the%20Earth.%20According%20to%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20Sun%20will%20reach%20%26quot%3Bsolar%20maximum%26quot%3B%20-%20a%20particularly%20active%20period%20-%20in%202025%20and%20today's%20digital%20world%20is%20not%20prepared%20for%20it.%20Terms%20like%20%26quot%3Binternet%20apocalypse%26quot%3B%20have%20caught%20the%20attention%20of%20social%20media%20users%2C%20which%20led%20to%20a%20barrage%20of%20misinformation%20and%20unsubstantiated%20warnings%20from%20American%20space%20agency%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20has%20not%20yet%20commented%20on%20the%20possibility%20of%20the%20end%20of%20the%20internet%20being%20caused%20by%20the%202025%20solar%20storm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20people%20started%20discussing%20what%20the%20%26quot%3Balways%20online%26quot%3B%20tribe%20will%20do%20if%20such%20an%20event%20takes%20place%3F%20But%20it%20is%20just%20a%20hype%3F%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftechnology%2F2023%2F06%2F28%2Fsolar-storm-internet-apocalypse%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EPost%3C%2Fem%3E%20says%3C%2Fa%3E%20these%20concerns%20are%20not%20entirely%20fiction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20strong%20solar%20storm%20could%20hit%20Earth%20-%20a%20rare%20event%20that%20has%20not%20happened%20in%20the%20interconnected%20world%20so%20far%20-%20causing%20widespread%20internet%20outage.%20It%20mentioned%20the%20Carrington%20Event%20in%201859%20due%20to%20which%20the%20telegraph%20lines%20sparked%20and%20operators%20were%20electrocuted%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%201989%20solar%20storm%20that%20took%20out%20the%20Quebec%20power%20grid%20for%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20never%20experienced%20one%20of%20the%20extreme%20case%20events%2C%20and%20we%20don't%20know%20how%20our%20infrastructure%20would%20respond%20to%20it.%20Our%20failure%20testing%20doesn't%20even%20include%20such%20scenarios%2C%26quot%3B%20Sangeetha%20Abdu%20Jyothi%2C%20a%20computer%20science%20professor%20at%20University%20of%20California%20at%20Irvine%2C%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3EPost%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20paper%20'Solar%20Superstorms%3A%20Planning%20for%20an%20Internet%20Apocalypse'%20played%20a%20key%20role%20in%20popularising%20the%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Jyothi%20said%20that%20a%20severe%20solar%20storm%20is%20likely%20to%20affect%20large-scale%20infrastructure%20such%20as%20undersea%20communication%20cables%20that%20could%20interrupt%20long-distance%20connectivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20outages%20could%20last%20for%20months%2C%20said%20the%20outlet%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20economic%20impact%20of%20just%20one%20day%20of%20lost%20connectivity%20in%20the%20US%20alone%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%20more%20than%20%2411%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20July%204%2C%20as%20the%20US%20celebrated%20its%20Independence%20Day%2C%20the%20Sun%20held%20its%20own%20firework%20display.%20Space%20weather%20physicist%20Tamitha%20Skov%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FTamithaSkov%2Fstatus%2F1676390737083265024%5C%22%3Eshared%20