0focus%20on%20transfer%20of%20technology%20like%20no%20other%20country%20does%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurther%2C%20India%20already%20has%20constructed%20six%20Scorpene-class%20submarines%20at%20Mazgaon%20Dockyards.%20But%2C%20as%20%3Cem%3EET%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%2C%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20would%20also%20like%20three%20more%20of%20these%20French-origin%20submarines%2C%20which%20is%20urgently%20required%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20ageing%20fleet%20of%20Russian-origin%20submarines%20get%20retired.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%2C%20India%20will%20also%20be%20looking%20to%20procure%2026%20Rafale%20M%20Combat%20naval%20aircraft%2C%20which%20includes%2022%20single-seater%20and%20four%20double-seater%20trainer%20jets%2C%20as%20per%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.financialexpress.com%2Fbusiness%2Fdefence-forging-a-naval-alliance-india-and-france-to-boost-defence-capabilities-3165009%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFinancial%20Express%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20three%20proposals%20have%20already%20been%20cleared%20by%20the%20Defence%20Procurement%20Board%2C%20but%20now%20require%20clearance%20from%20the%20Defence%20Acquisition%20Council%2C%20chaired%20by%20defence%20minister%20Rajnath%20Singh.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sipri.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2023-03%2F2303_at_fact_sheet_2022_v2.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20the%20Stockholm%20International%20Peace%20Research%20Institute%20(SIPRI)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20between%202018%20and%202022%2C%20France%20was%20India%E2%80%99s%20second%20largest%20arms%20supplier%2C%20accounting%20for%2029%25%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20imports.%20Russia%20accounted%20for%20nearly%20half%20(45%25)%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20arms%20imports%20during%20the%20same%20period.%20India%20was%20the%20largest%20recipient%20of%20France%E2%80%99s%20total%20global%20arms%20export%20during%20the%20same%20period%2C%20with%20a%20share%20of%2022%25.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20SIPRI%20report%20also%20observed%20that%20French%20defence%20exports%20to%20India%2C%20which%20have%20included%2062%20aircraft%20and%20four%20submarines%2C%20have%20increased%20by%20489%25%20between%202013-17%20and%202018-22.%20The%20French%20displaced%20the%20Americans%2C%20who%20trailed%20Russia%20in%20selling%20arms%20to%20India%20during%20the%202013-17%20period.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Findia-myanmar-weapons-modi-macron%5C%22%3EMyanmar%20Activists%20Urge%20Macron%20to%20Discuss%20With%20Modi%20India%E2%80%99s%20Sale%20of%20Weapons%20to%20Junta%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDefence%20ties%20have%20been%20robust%20%E2%80%93%20but%20what%20about%20economic%20cooperation%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20interviews%2C%20the%20French%20ambassador%20didn%E2%80%99t%20reveal%20the%20agreements%20that%20were%20in%20place%20but%20said%20that%20they%20would%20be%20in%20the%20sectors%20of%20defence%2C%20space%2C%20green%20hydrogen%20and%20people-to-people%20ties.%20Indian%20official%20sources%20added%20that%20there%20will%20be%20additional%20agreements%20in%20geo-strategy%2C%20infrastructure%2C%20climate%20action%2C%20museology%2C%20student%20mobility%2C%20sports%20and%20culture.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20report%20of%20the%20French%20national%20assembly%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20affairs%20committee%20this%20year%20lamented%20that%20the%20trade%20volume%20in%20%E2%80%9Cnormal%20times%E2%80%9D%20was%20usually%20around%2011-12%20billion%20euros.%20It%20increased%20by%20around%2019%25%20in%202022%2C%20as%20per%20French%20government%20figures%2C%20to%20around%2015.1%20billion%20euros.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20increase%20was%20reportedly%20due%20to%20a%20hike%20in%20French%20imports%20of%20refined%20petroleum%20products%20after%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20by%20Russia.%20France%20stopped%20buying%20Russian%20oil%20after%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%20Among%20European%20nations%2C%20it%20was%20not%20heavily%20reliant%20%3C%2Fspan%3Eon%20Russian%20energy%20due%20to%20its%20civilian%20nuclear%20energy%20programme.%20But%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F06%2F18%2Fbusiness%2Ffrance-nuclear-power-russia.html%3FsearchResultPosition%3D6%5C%22%3Epartial%20shutdown%20of%20its%20nuclear%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E%20due%20to%20problems%20with%20its%20main%20operator%20came%20at%20a%20bad%20time%2C%20which%20led%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20exports%20of%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20India%20did%20not%20join%20the%20sanctions%20against%20Russia%2C%20Indian%20refiners%20ramped%20up%20imports%20of%20Russian%20crude%20which%20were%20then%20sold%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20trade%2C%20the%20imbalance%20is%20in%20favour%20of%20India%2C%20with%20the%20deficit%20against%20France%20soaring%20to%20around%203%20billion%20euros%20in%202022.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20investment%20front%2C%20the%20story%20is%20different.%20French%20direct%20investment%20in%20India%20amounts%20to%20around%2011%20billion%20euros%2C%20with%20116%20companies%20employing%20450%2C000%20people.%20In%20contrast%2C%20Indian%20investment%20in%20France%20is%20valued%20at%20only%20200%20million%20euros%2C%20with%20fifty%20Indian%20companies%20employing%203%2C000%20people.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20area%20of%20interest%20for%20France%20is%20the%20negotiations%20for%20an%20India-European%20Union%20Free%20Trade%20Agreement.%20The%20French%20view%20seems%20to%20be%20while%20the%20conclusion%20of%20an%20FTA%20would%20help%20in%20rebalancing%20ties%20with%20China%2C%20it%20would%20only%20be%20acceptable%20if%20it%20was%20sufficiently%20ambitious.%20This%20was%20in%20contrast%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20approach%20to%20forge%20an%20initial%20limited%20agreement%20that%20would%20remove%20tariffs%20on%20certain%20products%20that%20will%20favour%20Indian%20exporters.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHow%20does%20France%20view%20India%E2%80%99s%20position%20in%20the%20current%20geopolitical%20situation%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20current%20golden%20period%20in%20India-France%20ties%20can%20be%20traced%20to%20the%201998%20nuclear%20tests%2C%20when%20Paris%20was%20the%20first%20major%20power%20to%20open%20talks%20with%20New%20Delhi%2C%20which%20evolved%20into%20a%20strategic%20dialogue.%20France%20had%20also%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Funion-divided-over-indias-nuclear-tests%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eopposed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20imposing%20sanctions%20on%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIncidentally%2C%20France%20had%20become%20the%20third-party%20supplier%20of%20fuel%20to%20the%20Tarapur%20reactor%2C%20with%20blessings%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20sanctions%20triggered%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20nuclear%20test.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrance%20often%20looks%20at%20India%20as%20having%20a%20similar%20view%20on%20strategic%20autonomy%2C%20with%20both%20countries%20balancing%20relations%20with%20either%20%E2%80%98camps%E2%80%99.%20Macron%20was%2C%20perhaps%2C%20the%20only%20major%20Western%20leader%20to%20have%20sustained%20a%20personal%20relationship%20with%20his%20Russian%20and%20Chinese%20counterparts.%20His%20remarks%20about%20European%20position%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20Taiwan%2C%20which%20he%20later%20clarified%2C%20were%20greeted%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.worldpoliticsreview.com%2Feurope-strategic-autonomy-eu-us-france-relations-macron%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eindignant%20objections%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20Atlantic%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20most%20practitioners%20and%20observers%2C%20the%20key%20strategic%20convergence%20between%20India%20and%20France%20is%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrance%20considers%20itself%20an%20Indo-Pacific%20power%20through%20its%20overseas%20territories%2C%20which%20account%20for%20nine%20million%20square%20kilometres%20of%20EEZ%20in%20the%20region.%20While%20India%E2%80%99s%20Indo-Pacific%20position%20is%20based%20on%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20speech%20at%20the%20Shangri-La%20Dialogue%20in%202018%2C%20France%20unveiled%20its%20Strategy%20a%20year%20later%20which%20underlined%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9Cattempts%20and%20temptations%20at%20hegemony%20division%20or%20confrontation%20must%20be%20discouraged%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrance%20faced%20a%20setback%20over%20the%20formation%20of%20AUKUS%20in%202021%2C%20which%20led%20Australia%20to%20scrap%20its%20%2490%20billion%20contract%20with%20France%20for%20submarines.%20France%20and%20Australia%20have%20since%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lowyinstitute.org%2Fthe-interpreter%2Ffrance-australia-salving-wounds-aukus%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enormalised%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20their%20ties%2C%20but%20the%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2021%2Fsep%2F16%2Fstab-in-the-back-french-fury-australia-scraps-submarine-deal%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estab%20in%20the%20back%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20had%20then%20led%20French%20strategists%20to%20opine%20that%20Paris%20should%20%E2%80%9Cfully%20bank%20on%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFollowing%20the%20signing%20of%20a%20logistics%20support%20agreement%2C%C2%A0%20Indian%20naval%20ships%20can%20make%20technical%20stops%20in%20French%20territories%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%2C%20while%20French%20ships%20could%20do%20the%20same%20in%20Indian%20ports.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F12%2FINS_Vikramaditya_in_Baltic_Sea.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F12%2FINS_Vikramaditya_in_Baltic_Sea.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F12%2FINS_Vikramaditya_in_Baltic_Sea-300x188.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F12%2FINS_Vikramaditya_in_Baltic_Sea-1024x640.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F12%2FINS_Vikramaditya_in_Baltic_Sea-80x50.jpg%2080w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-16667%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EINS%20Vikramaditya%20at%20sea.%20Photo%3A%20Indian%20Navy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWill%20Ukraine%20figure%20in%20talks%20with%20India%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Ukraine%20war%20will%20certainly%20figure%20during%20the%20talks%2C%20but%20largely%20to%20take%20stock%20of%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20assessments.%20The%20French%20ambassador%20had%20said%20that%20France%E2%80%99s%20approach%20%E2%80%9Cis%20not%20to%20preach%20or%20try%20to%20put%20pressure%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CForeign%20policy%20is%20grounded%20in%20facts%20and%20reality%20and%20each%20country%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20works%20within%20its%20constraints%20and%20interests.%20We%20have%20our%20own%20constraints%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20last%20week.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20a%20strategic%20divergence%20in%20how%20France%20and%20India%20view%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%20For%20Paris%2C%20the%20conflict%20has%20global%20dimensions%2C%20with%20implications%20for%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20territorial%20integrity%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20Russia%20were%20to%20prevail%2C%20other%20countries%2C%20such%20as%20China%2C%20could%20take%20advantage%20of%20this%20experience%20to%20give%20free%20rein%20to%20their%20imperialist%20aspirations%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20report%20of%20the%20National%20Assembly%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20affairs%20committee.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%2C%20like%20most%20other%20developing%20nations%2C%20considers%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20as%20a%20European%20conflict%2C%20which%20has%20an%20economic%20impact%20on%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20food%20and%20energy%20security.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%2C%20which%20was%20published%20after%20a%20visit%20of%20the%20committee%20members%20to%20India%20in%20March%20to%20meet%20with%20the%20Indian%20establishment%2C%20also%20believed%20the%20time%20was%20ripe%20for%20France%20to%20attempt%20to%20wean%20India%20away%20from%20Russia.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20New%20Delhi%2C%20the%20relationship%20with%20Russia%20appears%20as%20a%20heritage%2C%20an%20asset%20but%20also%2C%20and%20increasingly%2C%20as%20a%20headache.%C2%A0The%20time%20is%20therefore%20well%20chosen%20to%20further%20strengthen%2C%20and%20over%20the%20long%20term%2C%20our%20strategic%20partnership%20with%20India%2C%20in%20the%20military%20and%20energy%20sectors%2C%20but%20also%20in%20economic%20and%20environmental%20matters%2C%20where%20the%20margins%20for%20progress%20are%20the%20strongest%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689088531000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F11202742%2FThe_Prime_Minister_Shri_Narendra_Modi_meeting_the_President_of_France_Mr._Emmanuel_Macron_at_Elysee_Palace_in_Paris_on_June_03_2017_2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewir